# UI Context

## Theme

FlowForge uses a **dark-first SaaS design system** inspired by developer tools and modern workflow platforms.

The interface is designed to feel like a **technical control plane**:
- deep dark backgrounds
- layered surfaces for hierarchy
- subtle borders for structure
- strong accent color for actions and states
- minimal visual noise, maximum clarity

No light mode exists. The product is intentionally optimized for long-duration professional use.

---

## Colors

All styling must use CSS variables only. No hardcoded hex values.

| Role            | CSS Variable        | Value (example) |
| --------------- | ------------------- | --------------- |
| Page background | `--bg-base`        | #0B0F17 |
| Surface         | `--bg-surface`     | #111827 |
| Elevated surface| `--bg-elevated`    | #1A2232 |
| Primary text    | `--text-primary`   | #E5E7EB |
| Muted text      | `--text-muted`     | #9CA3AF |
| Primary accent  | `--accent-primary` | #6366F1 |
| Accent hover    | `--accent-hover`   | #4F46E5 |
| Border          | `--border-default` | #243041 |
| Error           | `--state-error`    | #EF4444 |
| Success         | `--state-success`  | #22C55E |
| Warning         | `--state-warning`  | #F59E0B |

---

## Typography

Typography follows a clean developer-tool aesthetic with high readability.

| Role      | Font                | Variable      |
| --------- | ------------------- | ------------- |
| UI text   | Inter / Geist Sans  | `--font-sans` |
| Code/mono | JetBrains Mono      | `--font-mono` |

Rules:
- UI text must be sans-serif only
- Code, logs, and workflow outputs must use monospace
- Avoid decorative or display fonts

---

## Border Radius

The system uses a consistent radius scale to maintain visual hierarchy:

| Context           | Class              |
| ----------------- | ------------------ |
| Inline elements   | `rounded-sm`       |
| Buttons / inputs  | `rounded-md`       |
| Cards / panels    | `rounded-lg`       |
| Modals / overlays | `rounded-xl`       |

---

## Component Library

- Built on top of shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS
- All base UI components live in `/components/ui`
- Components must be composable and reusable
- No custom one-off UI logic inside pages

Rules:
- Prefer extending existing UI components over rewriting
- Use variant-based styling patterns (button variants, card variants)
- Keep UI logic separate from business logic

---

## Layout Patterns

### Dashboard Layout
- Left sidebar navigation (fixed width)
- Main content area (scrollable)
- Optional right panel for details/inspector views

---

### Workflow Editor Layout
- Center canvas for workflow definition
- Sidebar for nodes / inputs
- Inspector panel for selected node configuration

---

### Modals
- Centered overlay
- Background blur with dark opacity layer
- Escape key must close modal

---

### Tables / Data Views
- Dense layout for execution history
- Row hover highlights
- Status badges for workflow runs

---

### Navigation
- Persistent sidebar navigation
- Active route highlighting using accent color
- Icons + labels (collapsed mode supported)

---

## Icons

- Lucide React is the default icon system
- Stroke-based icons only
- Standard sizing:
  - `h-4 w-4` → inline text/icons
  - `h-5 w-5` → buttons
  - `h-6 w-6` → headers / emphasis

Rules:
- Do not mix icon libraries
- Do not use filled icons
- Keep icon usage minimal and functional

---

## UI Principles

- Information density > decorative design
- Every UI element must serve a functional purpose
- Prioritize clarity over visual complexity
- Maintain consistent spacing scale across all components
- Avoid unnecessary animations unless they communicate state

---

## Interaction Patterns

- Loading states must always be explicit (skeletons or spinners)
- Actions that trigger workflows must show immediate feedback
- Execution states must be visually distinguishable:
  - queued
  - running
  - success
  - failed
- Real-time updates should update UI without full refresh